source: crates/kul-wasm/tests/format.rs
expression: formatted
---
# Example 9: Multiple adoptions for one child (P16).
#
# - Sam is biologically born to Ravi and Priya (1982).
# - Sam is first adopted by Anita and Bharat in 1985 (`m_anita_bharat`).
# - Sam is later adopted by Chen and Dara in 1992 (`m_chen_dara`).
#
# P16 designates the **most-recent** adoption as canonical: Sam's
# canonical card sits in `m_chen_dara`'s children row. Each earlier
# adoptive family displays a *child-ghost* of Sam at the past
# adoption's bar, connected by a dashed adoption edge. Per P16 the
# bar of `m_anita_bharat` is rendered even though no other rule would
# surface it — the child-ghost is the load-bearing reason it must
# exist. A solid biological cross-edge from Sam's canonical card to
# `m_ravi_priya` completes the picture.

# ---- Biological origin ----
person ravi   name:"Ravi Mehta"   gender:male    born:1958-01-14
person priya  name:"Priya Mehta"  gender:female  born:1960-04-22
marriage m_ravi_priya ravi priya  start:1980-11-10

# ---- First (now past) adoptive family ----
person anita   name:"Anita Rao"   gender:female  born:1952-06-08
person bharat  name:"Bharat Rao"  gender:male    born:1950-12-30
marriage m_anita_bharat anita bharat  start:1975-03-22

# ---- Second (canonical) adoptive family ----
person chen  name:"Chen Liu"  gender:male    born:1955-09-09
person dara  name:"Dara Liu"  gender:female  born:1957-02-17
marriage m_chen_dara chen dara  start:1980-07-04

# ---- Sam: bio + two adoptions in declaration order ----
person sam  name:"Sam"  gender:other  born:1982-05-19
  birth m_ravi_priya
  adoption m_anita_bharat  start:1985-04-01
  adoption m_chen_dara     start:1992-08-15
